  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6840.16 sitting just above the GEX flip at 6838, dealers are in positive gamma territory and likely selling delta into this 4.2% rip to hedge their long gamma positions. The massive +57M gamma wall at 6850 creates a strong magnet effect, but dealers will increasingly sell rallies as spot approaches that level, creating natural resistance. Given the PIN regime and dense positive gamma structure above current levels, expect mean-reverting behavior with upside capped near the 6850 max gamma strike.\n\nKey levels: watch for support at the 6838 flip and resistance building into 6850 where dealer selling pressure peaks.\n\n**Bottom line:** Prices should grind higher toward 6850 but face increasing selling pressure as they get there.",
